events.name: San Antonio Spurs at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Dejounte Murray could feel his annoyance building as San Antonio coaches repeatedly went back over video of the Spurs' blowout loss to New Orleans in the previous meeting between the two Western Conference play-in hopefuls.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray's triple-double lifts Spurs over Pelicans 107-103

headlines.description: — Pascal Siakam scored 23 points and the Toronto Raptors routed the depleted Indiana Pacers 131-91 on Saturday night in a game delayed 70 minutes in the first half because of a speaker fire that forced the evacuation of fans.
headlines.shortLinkText: Raptors rout Pacers after fire causes delay, fan evacuation

headlines.description: — When things got tight down the stretch, the Bulls' experience — and their All-Star power — showed up.
headlines.shortLinkText: LaVine's 25 lead Bulls to 98-94 win over young Cavaliers

headlines.description: — Goran Dragic looked up at the overhead screen and watched the video that paid tribute to his seven seasons with the Miami Heat, then waved to...
headlines.shortLinkText: Nets add to Miami's misery, rolling past Heat 110-95

headlines.description: — De’Anthony Melton had 24 points, Desmond Bane added 20 and the Memphis Grizzlies continued to win in the absence of scoring leader Ja Morant, beating the Milwaukee Bucks 127-102 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Melton, Bane lead Morant-less Grizzlies past Bucks, 127-102

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Denver Nuggets

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 35 points and 12 rebounds to help the Denver Nuggets fend off the scrappy Oklahoma City Thunder 113-107 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 35 in Nuggets' 113-107 win over Oklahoma City

events.name: Houston Rockets at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun scored 27 points off the bench, Jalen Green had 25 points and the Houston Rockets defeated the Portland Trail Blazers 115-98 on Saturday night to complete a back-to-back sweep.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun scores 27 as Rockets beat Trail Blazers again
